    {
      "@id": "#pangarra",
      "@type": "RepositoryObject",
      "name": "pangarra",
      "datePublished": "2016-11-08 01:36:17",
      "custom:translation": "Corella",
      "custom:sentence": "Pangarra-ma marnana yakakyakakkarra. Maitbi ngumpit yanana ngulu wuyurrunkarra-nginyi. Nguyina na kurru-ma nyangana. Nyantu na tiwu yanana kamparra yakakyakakkarra. Lintarr na nguyina marnana. \"Nyila nyila kurru nyangka-lu yakakyakakkarra pangarra. Maitbi ngulu yanana ngumpit, kuya, wuyurrunkarra-nginyi.",
      "custom:sentenceTranslation": "The corella calls out \"Yakak yakak!\" for example when people are returning from fishing. We hear it as it flies ahead of them calling out. It signals us that way. \"Hey listen to the corella calling. Maybe they're coming back from fishing!\"",
      "custom:photographerName": "Ian Montgomery",
      "custom:scientificName": "Cacatua sanguinea",
      "pcdm:memberOf": {
        "@id": "./"
      },
      "speaker": {
